Building Container Images with Advanced Dockerfile Instructions
oc new-project testci
oc new-app --name testci --strategy docker https://github.com/ratnamalubelli/DO288-apps#ics --context-dir container-build
oc get pods
oc logs -f bc/testci
oc logs containername
see that it shows errors for port number and permission denied
Go to cd DO288-apps/container-build
cat Dockerfile
edit to add permissions as below
Expose 8080
RUN sed -i "s/Listen 80/Listen 8080/g" /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf
RUN chgrp -R 0 /var/log/httpd /var/run/httpd && chmod -R g=u /var/log/httpd /var/run/httpd
